                        <caption>Schematic representation of the outer electron cloud of a neutral water molecule. The electrons spend more time near the oxygen than the hydrogens, giving a permanent charge separation as shown. Water is thus a <emphasis effect="italics">polar molecule</emphasis>. It is more easily affected by electrostatic forces than molecules with uniform charge distributions.</caption></figure></para>
