            <exercise id="fs-id2670145" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1425309">        <para id="import-auto-id1935840">(a) How strong is the attractive force between a glass rod with a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>0.700</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>μ</m:mi><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> charge and a silk cloth with a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>–0.600</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>μ</m:mi><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> charge, which are 12.0 cm apart, using the approximation that they act like point charges? (b) Discuss how the answer to this problem might be affected if the charges are distributed over some area and do not act like point charges.</para></problem>
                <solution id="fs-id2621989">
