            <exercise id="fs-id1362193" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2598838">        <para id="import-auto-id2684000">(a) Two point charges totaling <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>8.00</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>µ</m:mi><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> exert a repulsive force of 0.150 N on one another when separated by 0.500 m. What is the charge on each? (b) What is the charge on each if the force is attractive?</para></problem></exercise>
            <exercise id="fs-id2622925" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2209862">        <para id="import-auto-id1889286">Point charges of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>5.00</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>µ</m:mi><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>–3.00</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mi>µ</m:mi><m:mtext>C</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> are placed 0.250 m apart. (a) Where can a third charge be placed so that the net force on it is zero? (b) What if both charges are positive?</para></problem>
